            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I wonder whether the issue reported here is resolved by [the last option listed here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/6584#issuecomment-373688975).\r\n\r\nI landed here while experiencing this issue arising from a completely different set-up (e.g., no gruvbox, NVIM v0.4.3, different version of iTerm2), and what resolved my issue after much experimentation was the fact that i had been setting `hi Cursor guifg=white guibg=None`. My suspicion is that if the cursor styling is set incorrectly _and not reset_ (as described helpfully [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/wiki/FAQ#cursor-style-isnt-restored-after-exiting-nvim)), then these `ff` artifacts will appear:\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n\" tmp.vim\r\nset termguicolors\r\n\r\nhi lCursor guifg=white guibg=None\r\nset guicursor=n:block-lCursor\r\n```\r\nand then: `$ nvim -u tmp.vim`:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5423134/83932349-797e1e80-a767-11ea-8031-1fbcac55205f.png)\r\n\r\nMaybe this is old news; figured I'd leave a note in case the OP is still dealing with this, someone wanders over here from a search engine, or the maintainers would like to close this issue out (assuming this prognosis is accurate).",
